.Maxwellian-averaged cross-sections were calculated
for energy interval 0-700 keV by dividing it into
three parts according cross-section's sources.
The contribution I-1 was determined by normalizing the
cross sections of Kopecky (see REL-REF) to the present
data in the interval between 3 to 15 keV.
The dominant part I-2 between 3 and 225 keV is provided
by the present experiment. These data were obtained by
sufficient resolution in neutron energy to exclude
systematic uncertainties that may result in calculation
of the Maxwellian average if the energy grid is too
coarse.
At typical s-process temperatures the energy interval
from 225 to 700 keV contributes very little to the
Maxwellian average. For this part, the data of
Kopecky (see REL-REF) were normalized to the present
results between 50 and 225 keV.
Total error
Statistical uncertainty
total systematic error of Maxwell. averaging
Systematic uncertainties are correspond to the
uncertainties of the cross section ratios.
The 1.5% uncertainty of the gold standard is not
included here, since it cancels out in most
applications of relevance for nuclear astrophysics
- data for I-1 and
I-3 intervals were taken from this ref. and normalized
to present experiment
Data from Table VIII  of PR/C,66,(2),025801
and Tbl.21 of FZKA-6619
